<li><b>Change 1.6.2 to fix an erratum</b>.  While the exercise was
doable, the hint was for the version that really mattered, which is
restriction to lines (not hyperplanes) being countable.  So change
it to lines.  Same idea, but now as intended.
<li>Just before the proof of Theorem 1.6.6, the normal form for a function
of one variable is better stated for nonconstant functions to avoid
the nonsense of taking \(d=0.\)
